Oh, and if u select 'roasted vegetables' as your main, don't be surprised if you get  just lots of carrots and almost none of the delicious Brussels sprouts and cauliflower that are on full display--if you want some, you often have to ask for them to be added, which is a pain.

Would like to start off by saying I love Cava's food, and have never had problem with the meals there. It is for this reason why I was so disappointed after my visit there this afternoon. I stepped up in line (with 3 or 4 people behind me) and started to place my order. I immediately got a clear indication that the employee had no interest in being there or serving me. When I asked to sample the new rice that was advertised outside the entrance, she gave me an almost comically obvious sigh in sign of exasperation as if I had just ruined her day. For every following item that I added to my order, she either rolled her eyes, sighed or showed some other rude sign of discontent. Meanwhile, my friend who was right behind me in line was being rushed at a ridiculous pace by the employee helping him. The whole situation was so ludicrous that it could have belonged in a skit. Seeing that similar reviews have recently been posted regarding their customer service, it was disheartening, and I can't say that we will be returning to this particular location.

Offers the best tasting, customized salad combinations  you will ever eat!   You can SMELL this salad.  The salad AND the salad bowl always smell great!  Very easy to customize.  Use the Cava smartphone application to order to maximize your options.  However, you cannot order online while in a Cava restaurant; order online before you enter the restaurant.  If you like a particular salad item, like fresh tomatoes, you can do a double-click in the application and get a double order of tomatoes on your salad.  Salads are so rich, they really do not need a dressing.  However, get dressing on the side just to taste some wonderful sauces.  The fresh beverages (cold tea and lemonade) are not to be missed.  They are ALL very good and made with pure natural cane sugar.  You can order ahead either to take out or eat in the restaurant.  Nice space for solo dining  Only paper bowls and plastic cultery for all meals.  No real dishes and cultery (and wine/beer) and waiter service like Noodles & Co.when you dine inside the restaurant  Staff are great and are comfortable with specialized requests.
